displayName: City of Oros in the mountains

parameters:
Clea: Is this the mountain city of Oros? It's quite
impressive compared to Valie.

Nora the Thief: The smell is different! The smell of bread
seems more delicious than in a normal town.

Mage Relm: What is that...? This is the place where the
Empire's greatest crystal mine is located, you know.

Cleric Sophia: Ohoho, a place where both money and people
gather. I'm looking forward to the variety of drinks at the
tavern.

Swift Celis: There should be a bulletin board at the tavern.
I think Clea and the others can handle many things now.

Swift Celis: First, let's complete this request and then we
can all go collect the crystals together.
Clea: Celis-san, you seem to be having fun.

Swift Celis: I might be a little excited because there are
so many solo missions... I'm sorry.
Cleric Sophia: Oh my, she can make such expressions too.
Mage Relm (Hehe, it seems like I'm the only adult here!)
Thief Nora (The smell of grilled chicken... sounds so good)
Oros Guard: Entry is prohibited for civilians here.

Celis the Swift: I am Celis, from the Adventurer's Guild. I
have come to collect the requested item.

Oros Guard: Understood, let the director know that we have a
visitor!

Oros Guard: Please, the director is waiting for you in the
warehouse.
Oros Guard: Leave the defense of the warehouse to us!
Oros Guard: Leave the defense of the warehouse to us!

Crystal Merchant: The Empire is the best! They give me so
many gold coins that they overflow from my pockets!

Crystal Merchant: The Empire is the best! They give me so
many gold coins that they overflow from my pockets!

Noblewoman: Isn't the cityscape beautiful? It's all thanks
to the blessings of the crystals.

Noblewoman: Isn't the cityscape beautiful? It's all thanks
to the blessings of the crystals.

Noble Child: I went to Valdo's villa before! I want to go
play in the big forest and lake again!

Noble Child: I went to Valdo's villa before! I want to go
play in the big forest and lake again!

Traveling Jewel Merchant: 'Haha, those clothes don't suit
you, huh? In this town, they'll judge you based on what
you're wearing.'

Old man reminiscing, Thanks to the crystal, I became
wealthy... but I miss the old quiet mountain town of Oros.
